author: app.com
title: Skodim vaults Jackson Memorial field hockey to win over Brick
text:
MORE Kayla Skodim scored two first half goals and also assisted on a goal in each half as she led the No. 7 Jackson Memorial field hockey team to a 5-0 Class A South victory over Brick on Wednesday afternoon.
Skodmin tallied at 7:30 and 28:29 and assisted on goals by Amanda Miller (11:08) and Taryn Wilkins (41:57). Rebkekah Chin also scored at 12:30 and Jenny McNamara was credited with the assist. Morgan Novak and the Jaguars (9-1-1) defense didnâ€™t allow a shot on goal while Kylie Spinello made 13 saves for Brick (1-9-2).
IN OTHER FIELD HOCKEY
Southern 2, Toms River North 0: Madison Skeie and Zoe Sparks each had a goal while Keeley Winn had two assists and Nicole Andriani made five saves for the Rams (12-0) against the Mariners (6-5).
Toms River South 4, Toms River East 0: Hannah Claus and Jennifer Toal each had two goals and Caroline Toner had two assists as the Indians (6-4) defeated the Raiders (1-6-2) in a Class A South game. Toal also had an assist and Katie Schwartz added an assist.
Lacey 5, Brick Memorial 0 : Emily Dezendort had two goals and one assist, Trisha Ciernak added one goal and three assists and Carly Chimenti made one saves for the Lions (6-5-1) against the Mustangs (2-10).
